<HEADLINE>
TAF AWARD NOMINATION BEGINS
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Los Angeles,  March  13 (CNA) 03/14/07  16:32:50 (By Chu Lu-sheng
and Elizabeth Hsu)
</P>
<P>
The U.S.-based Taiwanese-American Foundation (TAF) has begun
nomination operations for the TAF Award that recognizes those who
love Taiwan and identify Taiwan as their homeland and who have
achieved outstanding accomplishment in the fields of engineering,
the humanities and social services, TAF executives said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The deadline of the nomination was set for June 3, with the award
presentation ceremony slated for November in Los Angeles, the TAF
said.
</P>
<P>
The non-profit TAF was founded in 1982 in Southern California by
successful entrepreneur Kenjohn Wang and his wife Jacqueline, who
are originally from Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Individuals, regardless of their ethnic origin, who love Taiwan
and recognize Taiwan as their home, are qualified to apply for
TAF awards by obtaining their nomination through a well-
established organization, according to the TAF, which said
application forms can be obtained  online at www.tafaward.com,
or by visiting  the foundation.
</P>
<P>
Over the past 25 years, there have been 57 TAF achievement awards
and eight special awards presented. The recipients of the TAF
Special Award in recognizing the individual who has significantly
contributed to Taiwan development include former President Lee
Teng-hui, Vice President Annette Lu and former Academia Sinica
President and Nobel Price laureate Lee Yuan-tseh.
</P>
